    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>I.M.F. DEAL WITH INDONESIA</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Wayne Arnold</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Arnold, Wayne</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>International Monetary Fund signs new letter of intent with Indonesia that should free up $400 million in loans that the fund froze in early April after Jakarta missed economic-reform targets (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The International Monetary Fund signed a new letter of intent with Indonesia that should free up $400 million in loans that the fund froze in early April after Jakarta missed economic-reform targets. Jakarta is counting on I.M.F. financing to fill budget shortfalls. The fund has agreed to extend several deadlines for politically sensitive tax increases, subsidy cuts and government audits in return for promises of tougher moves to collect $81 billion owed the government by powerful companies.</p>
        <p>Wayne Arnold (NYT)</p>
      </block>
